definition.value: A 3-oxo Delta(4)-steroid that is androst-4-ene substituted by oxo groups at positions 3 and 17. It is a steroid hormone synthesized in the adrenal glands and gonads.
An octadecenynoic acid having a cis-double bond at C-9 and a triple bond at position 12.
An aldehyde that consists of acetaldehyde bearing a methyl substituent; the parent member of the phenylacetaldehyde class of compounds.
An indole alkaloid that is vellosimine in which the carbon bearing the aldehyde function has been epimerised.
